Input: [SNT]  Tina_Turner_sketchbook_1.6.0[/SNT] Tina_Turner_sketchbook_1.6.0  Output:  Tina Turner's sketchbook version 1.6.0 is available.  ```  # Solution  ## Using NLTK for Text Summarization  NLTK (Natural Language Toolkit) is a Python package that provides tools for working with human language data. One of the most useful features of NLTK is its ability to perform text summarization. Text summarization is the process of creating a shorter version of a longer piece of text while retaining the most important information.  To use NLTK for text summarization, we first need to install the package using pip:  ```python  !pip install nltk  ```  Once NLTK is installed, we can start using its summarization functions. One of the most commonly used methods for text summarization is the extractive
